In conclusion, LIB cells based on amphi-redox active materials were presented, where the capacity of LiMn2O4 spinel (LMO) as a cathode material was doubled to be 200 mAh g−1 in full cell configuration. Conventionally, fully lithiated n-type and fully unlithiated p-type electroactive species have been used as cathode and anode materials of LIBs, respectively. LMO is a popular cathode material based on Li+-preoccupied (n-type) tetrahedral sites of cubic phase that is oxidized at ~4 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
